'''Lennox Cooper''' (date of birth unknown) is a former [[West Indies cricket team|West Indian]] [[cricket]]er. Cooper's [[batsman (cricket)|batting]] style is unknown, though it is known he bowled right-arm [[Fast bowling|fast]]. He was born on [[Montserrat]].

Cooper first played for [[Montserrat cricket team|Montserrat]] against [[St Kitts cricket team|St Kitts]] in the 1970 Hesketh Bell Shield.<ref name="MIS">{{cite web|url=http://www.cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/23/23421/Miscellaneous_Matches.html|title=Miscellaneous Matches played by Lennox Cooper|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=14 October 2012}}</ref> In 1971, he made a single [[first-class cricket|first-class]] appearance for the [[Leeward Islands cricket team|Leeward Islands]] against the [[Windward Islands cricket team|Windward Islands]] at [[Warner Park Sporting Complex|Warner Park, St Kitts]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/23/23421/First-Class_Matches.html|title=First-Class Matches played by Lennox Cooper|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=14 October 2012}}</ref> Batting first, the Windward Islands were dismissed for 122, with Cooper bowling four wicketless [[over (cricket)|overs]] which conceded 15 runs. In reply, the Leeward Islands made 315 all out in their first-innings, with Cooper ending the innings [[not out|unbeaten]] on 3. Responding in their second-innings, the Windward Islands were dismissed for 153, with Cooper taking a single wicket in the innings, that of Windward Islands [[captain (cricket)|captain]] [[Irvine Shillingford]], finishing with figures of 1/32 from fifteen overs. The Leeward Islands won the match by the margin of an innings and 40 runs.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/31/31385.html|title=Leeward Islands v Windward Islands, 1970/71|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=14 October 2012}}</ref> He played three minor matches for Montserrat in 1971, before [[emigration|emigrating]] to [[Canada]].<ref name="MIS"/>

